d the body. In addition, they highlight Esposito's reading and interpretation of classical political thinkers, including Hobbes, Machiavelli, Vico, Arendt, and Kant. The book explores applications of Esposito's philosophy to issues in international relations, post-colonialism, literature, science, technology, and philosophical and artistic practice, bringing Esposito into dialogue with important social-political concerns.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aBiopoliticsxPhilosophy. 0aInternational relationsxPhilosophy. 0aPolitical sciencexPhilosophy. 4aPhilosophy : Continental Philosophy. 4aPhilosophy : Philosophy. 4aPolitics and Law : Political Philosophy. 4aPolitics and Law : Political Theory. 7aPHILOSOPHY / General.2bisacsh1 aBertland, Alexander U., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBird, Greg, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCalcagno, Antonio, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCalcagno, Antonio, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aEnns, Diane, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFridman, Federico, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHanafin, Patrick, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLuisetti, Federico, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMoreiras, Alberto, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aN. Franke, Mark F., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aShort, Jonathan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aViriasova, Inna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aViriasova, Inna, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators